cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new convolutional operation that improves the efficiency and accuracy of convolutional neural networks for image and video recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the impact of the proposed method on the network architecture and computational cost, which suggests that it could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper includes experiments on image and video recognition tasks, which could also make it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
